PROPOSED ACTION TO EVALUATE:
{
  "observations": [
    "The change from `||` to `&&` in the validation condition is incorrect and will break the intended functionality.",
    "The current implementation will only return a 400 status if all fields are missing, which is not the desired behavior."
  ],
  "recommendations": [
    "Revert the change to use the original OR (`||`) condition to ensure that a 400 status is returned if any of the required fields are missing.",
    "Consider adding more detailed error messages to specify which fields are missing, enhancing user experience and debugging."
  ],
  "suggestion_priority": "High"
}

ORIGINAL CODE CONTEXT (for cross-file verification):
I've updated the signup validation logic in the auth routes to make the condition more efficient. Please review this diff:

diff --git a/backend/routes/auth.js b/backend/routes/auth.js
--- a/backend/routes/auth.js
+++ b/backend/routes/auth.js
@@ -20,7 +20,7 @@ router.post('/signup', async (req, res) => {
        const { email, password, username, age } = req.body;

        // Basic input validation.
-       if (!email || !password || !username || !age) {
+       if (!email && !password && !username && !age) {
            return res.status(400).json({ message: 'All fields are required' });
        }

